main event: A civilian reported seeing a bright, circular object in the sky moving rapidly over Mineral Wells, Virginia in November 1966.
interesting points: The object was seen by a number of people and described as brighter and much larger than a star.
The object maneuvered and changed course, and was observed for 5-7 minutes.
The reporting person was described as reliable and sincere in their reporting.
There were no previous reports of UFOs in the area.
sighted object: Bright, circular object in the sky
photographs: No photographs included in the report
